<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb971124c-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3" identifier="/us/usc/t39/s3684"><num value="3684">§ 3684.</num><heading> Limitations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Except as provided in <ref href="/us/usc/t39/s3627">section 3627 of this title</ref>, no provision of this chapter shall be construed to give authority to the Governors to make any change in any provision of this title.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb971124d-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3">(<ref href="/us/pl/91/375">Pub. L. 91–375</ref>, <date date="1970-08-12">Aug. 12, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/765">84 Stat. 765</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/99/410/tII/s201/b/4">Pub. L. 99–410, title II, § 201(b)(4)</ref>, <date date="1986-08-28">Aug. 28, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/929">100 Stat. 929</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/109/435/tX/s1010/f">Pub. L. 109–435, title X, § 1010(f)</ref>, <date date="2006-12-20">Dec. 20, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/3262">120 Stat. 3262</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb971124e-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idb971124f-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idb9711250-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2006—<ref href="/us/pl/109/435">Pub. L. 109–435</ref> substituted “of this title” for “of section 3682 or 3683 or chapter 30, 32, or 34 of this title”.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1986—<ref href="/us/pl/99/410">Pub. L. 99–410</ref> struck out “, or of the Federal Voting Assistance Act of 1955” after “or 34 of this title”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idb9711251-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDateOfAmendment" id="idb9711252-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date of 1986 Amendment</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Amendment by <ref href="/us/pl/99/410">Pub. L. 99–410</ref> applicable with respect to elections taking place after <date date="1987-12-31">Dec. 31, 1987</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/99/410/s204">section 204 of Pub. L. 99–410</ref>, set out as an Effective Date note under <ref href="/us/usc/t52/s20301">section 20301 of Title 52</ref>, Voting and Elections.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idb9711253-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1971-01-20">Jan. 20, 1971</date>, pursuant to Resolution No. 71–10 of the Board of Governors. See <ref href="/us/pl/91/375/s15/a">section 15(a) of Pub. L. 91–375</ref>, set out as a note preceding <ref href="/us/usc/t39/s101">section 101 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
